Gymshark Train
We train. We motivate. We grow. Together.
Step up your game and join the family, so we can #GymsharkTrain together 🦈

Get ready to sweat with @scottw_jordan 💦 This epic full body workout can be done right from your living room floor. All you need is a set of dumbbells 💪 Let’s go Gymshark fam 🦈

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

#Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Get ready to make that full body work with this powerful at-home HIIT workout from @mrandmrsmuscle 💪 
Tag a friend who you would duo this with!
#Gymsharktrain

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

node.text:
@wozldn brings you a 🔥 full body workout to celebrate the last day of #Gymshark66! Expect 30 minutes of dynamic and energetic H.I.I.T exercises – you're defo going to need some water 🥵

Please only take part in the workout if you are medically and physically fit and have not been advised not to participate by a qualified medical professional. If your health or fitness changes adversely in any way before, during and/or after the workout please seek and follow medical advice without delay.

Click the link in our bio for more mobility workouts‼️ #Gymsharktrain

node.text:
Tuesday Choose-Day full body challenge 👭
Pick a partner and challenge them to join you in this @adotty10 + @littletfitness circuit by leaving an @ for them in the comments 🏆
1️⃣ 180 burpee jumps
2️⃣ Pushup clap + Dip
3️⃣ Alt. Bulgarian split squat
4️⃣ Reverse leg lifts
5️⃣ Bunny hops
45 secs on | 15 secs off | 4x rounds
#GymsharkTrain

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by @gymsharktrain on September 07, 2021 tagging @gymshark, @sophjbutler, @gymsharkwomen, and @gymsharktrain. May be an image of 1 person, biceps, standing and text that says 'CHEST 4 EXERCISES 3 SETS'.

node.text:
If you're in need of some chest day inspo, @sophjbutler has delivered the goods right here 🙌
Swipe + save:
1️⃣ Incline dumbbell chest press (1 warm-up set of 15 reps, then 3x10-12 active sets)
2️⃣ Incline dumbbell flyes (3x10-12)
3️⃣ Superset: Upright dumbbell flyes + Dumbbell punches (3x10-12 each)
4️⃣ Incline pinch press (3x12-15)
#GymsharkTrain

3 quick, simple + effective bicep exercises. No need to over complicate things ✔️
1️⃣ Seated bicep curls (4x10)
2️⃣ Seated hammer curls (4x10)
3️⃣ Straight bar curls (4x8-10)
📸: @elliotbfit
#GymsharkTrain

node.text:
Make your comeback to the gym with this ultimate leg day routine 🦵 🏋️‍♀️
1️⃣ 7-7-7 hip thrusts (3 sets)
2️⃣ DB double contraction sumo squat (3x10)
Superset with...
3️⃣ Double contraction RDL (3x10)
4️⃣ Box jump combo (3x8)
📸: @libbychristensen 
#GymsharkTrain

Here's the leg day routine you won't wanna miss this week 🔥
1️⃣ Squat (3x12)
2️⃣ Leg curl (3x8)
3️⃣ Single arm kettlebell front squat (3x8 each leg)
4️⃣ Dumbbell box step up (3x8)
5️⃣ Burpee to box jump (4x5)
We're here to see you make those moves and keep you pushing forwards. Tag us in your workout videos with #GymsharkTrain
📸: @m3colby

node.text:
Oh wow, this effective full body workout is our fave of the week 🙌
Routine:
1️⃣ Sumo deadlift
2️⃣ V-sits
3️⃣ Kettlebell swings
4️⃣ Kettlebell hanging squats
Extra info:
💡 Complete sumo deadlifts & V-sits one after the other. Repeat this 3x for as many reps as possible
💡 Complete swings, squats & taps one after another. Repeat this 3x for as many reps as possible
Share this training inspo with a friend who needs it 💪
📸: @sophthickfitnesss
#GymsharkTrain
